                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.5034 Registration/73: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gauss</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-05-22T13:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 22, 1944—1 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>695. Private source reports receipt of advice that Eichholver, President American
                    Chamber of Commerce, Chungking, stated at meeting early this month that it is
                    necessary to expedite registration by branch offices of American companies.
                    Please telegraph whether situation has changed since dispatch of your telegram
                    no. 540 of March 28, 1944.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
